asymmetric mobility SE1E2IIaR two strains

Source: R/asymmetric_mobility_se1e2iiar_2strains.R
asymmetric_mobility_se1e2iiar_2strains.Rd

For more information, look at vignette("commuter_model","spread")

Usage

asymmetric_mobility_se1e2iiar_2strains(
 
    se1e2iiar_2strains_pop = spread::asymmetric_mobility_se1e2iiar_dummy_se1e2iiar_2strains_pop,
  mobility_matrix = spread::asymmetric_mobility_se1e2iiar_dummy_mobility_matrix,
  dynamic_seeds = NULL,
  betas = spread::asymmetric_mobility_se1e2iiar_dummy_betas,
  inputSeed = as.numeric(Sys.time()),
  latent_period = 3,
  presymptomatic_period = 2,
  infectious_period = 5,
  b_relative_infectiousness = 1.5,
  presymptomatic_relative_infectiousness = 1.25,
  asymptomatic_prob = 0.4,
  asymptomatic_relative_infectiousness = 0.5,
  N = 1
)

Arguments

se1e2iiar_2strains_pop

Data frame containing `location_code`, `S`, `E1`, `E2`, `I`, `Ia`, `R`, `E1_b`, `E2_b`, `I_b`, and`Ia_b` for the entire population

mobility_matrix

List (1 entry for each time period) with each entry containing a data frame with `from`, `to`, `n` for the number of people who travel. Each data frame must be complete.

dynamic_seeds

Data.table containing `location_code`, `day`, `n`, `n_b` for dynamic seeding (or `NULL`)

betas

Data table with `locaton code`, `day`, `time`, `beta` (1 entry for each location for each time period). Float, infection parameter, 0.6

inputSeed

Integer with seed for cpp code

latent_period

Float, 3.0

presymptomatic_period

Float 2.0

infectious_period

Float, 5.0

b_relative_infectiousness

Float, relative infectiousness of strain B

presymptomatic_relative_infectiousness

Float, relative infectiousness of presymptomatic

asymptomatic_prob

Float, Proportion/probability of asymptomatic given infectious

asymptomatic_relative_infectiousness

Float, Relative infectiousness of asymptomatic infectious

N

Int = 1 int, Number of internal simulations (average taken). This is generally used for parameter fitting.

Value

A data.table containing the following variables:

location_code

Location code

week

Week number

day

Day number

time

Time of reporting (23:59)

b_S

Susceptibles belonging to location code

b_E1

E1s belonging to location code

b_E2

E2s belonging to location code

b_I

Infectious (symptomatic) belonging to location code

b_Ia

Infectious (asymptomatic) belonging to location code

b_R

Recovered belonging to location code

b_E1_b

E1_bs belonging to location code

b_E2_b

E2_bs belonging to location code

b_I_b

Infectious (symptomatic) strain B belonging to location code

b_Ia_b

Infectious (asymptomatic) strain B belonging to location code

c_S

Susceptibles currently in this location code

c_E1

E1s currently in this location code

c_E2

E2s currently in this location code

c_I

Infectious (symptomatic) currently in this location code

c_Ia

Infectious (asymptomatic) currently in this location code

c_R

Recovered currently in this location code

c_E1_b

E1_bs currently in this location code

c_E2_b

E2_bs currently in this location code

c_I_b

Infectious (symptomatic) strain B currently in this location code

c_Ia_b

Infectious (asymptomatic) strain B currently in this location code

c_symp_incidence_a

Transition from E2 to I currently in this location code

c_asymp_incidence_a

Transition from E1 to Ia currently in this location code

c_symp_incidence_b

Transition from E2_b to I_b currently in this location code

c_asymp_incidence_b

Transition from E1_b to Ia_b currently in this location code

c_symp_incidence

Transition from E2 and E2_b to I and I_b currently in this location code

c_asymp_incidence

Transition from E1 and E1_b to Ia and Ia_b currently in this location code

Examples

spread::asymmetric_mobility_se1e2iiar_2strains(
  se1e2iiar_2strains_pop = spread::asymmetric_mobility_se1e2iiar_dummy_se1e2iiar_2strains_pop,
  mobility_matrix = spread::asymmetric_mobility_se1e2iiar_dummy_mobility_matrix,
  dynamic_seeds = spread::asymmetric_mobility_se1e2iiar_2strains_dummy_dynamic_seeds,
  betas = spread::asymmetric_mobility_se1e2iiar_dummy_betas,
  inputSeed = 123,
  latent_period = 3.0,
  presymptomatic_period = 2.0,
  infectious_period = 5.0,
  b_relative_infectiousness = 1.5,
  presymptomatic_relative_infectiousness = 1,
  asymptomatic_prob = 0,
  asymptomatic_relative_infectiousness = 0,
  N = 1
)
